WEBVTT

00:02.710 --> 00:04.000
Previously on "Kevin (Probably)
Saves the World"....

00:04.000 --> 00:05.290
-I'm a messenger from God.
-Oh, good.

00:05.290 --> 00:06.920
I'm here to guide
and protect you.

00:06.920 --> 00:08.210
Who are you talking to?

00:08.210 --> 00:09.500
She can't see me.

00:09.500 --> 00:12.670
In every generation,
there are 36 righteous souls.

00:12.670 --> 00:15.460
The only job you have in life
for the foreseeable future

00:15.460 --> 00:16.790
is to build up
your spiritual powers

00:16.790 --> 00:19.170
through acts of kindness
and selflessness.

00:19.170 --> 00:20.380
After you've done so,

00:20.380 --> 00:21.380
God is gonna show you

00:21.380 --> 00:23.750
how to find
the other Righteous.

00:23.750 --> 00:25.710
We have to find out
where this is.

00:25.710 --> 00:27.250
That's where you'll find
the next righteous person.

00:27.250 --> 00:28.620
You've been here
this whole time?

00:28.620 --> 00:30.670
No, I've been in conference
with my colleagues.

00:30.670 --> 00:32.790
They're not really
feeling the mission anymore.

00:32.790 --> 00:34.080
We still have
a job to do.

00:34.080 --> 00:35.540
Mom!

00:35.540 --> 00:40.080
♪♪

00:40.080 --> 00:41.670
How'd you do that?

00:41.670 --> 00:42.880
I-- Sorr--
What are you talking about?

00:45.710 --> 00:50.080
Kevin: It all started
when I saw the butterflies.

00:50.080 --> 00:53.960
And then I wound up
in some lake.

00:53.960 --> 00:56.420
After that came the red masks,

00:56.420 --> 00:59.290
and there was mariachi music,
too.

00:59.290 --> 01:00.710
Still don't know how
that fits in.

01:00.710 --> 01:03.210
One by one,

01:03.210 --> 01:06.540
the universe
gave us clues --

01:06.540 --> 01:12.330
clues that will lead us
to our first righteous soul.

01:12.330 --> 01:14.960
Nice work, right?
Mm.

01:14.960 --> 01:16.830
What?
You don't like it?

01:16.830 --> 01:19.710
Well, all you did was
take the photos

01:19.710 --> 01:21.380
and pin them up
with yarn.

01:21.380 --> 01:22.620
Y-- [ Sighs ]

01:22.620 --> 01:25.040
No, this is a murder board.
[ Scoffs ]

01:25.040 --> 01:26.620
What's a murder board?

01:26.620 --> 01:28.960
It's what detectives
on TV use

01:28.960 --> 01:31.710
to -- to solve crimes
and nail perps.

01:31.710 --> 01:33.040
Have you never seen
a cop show?

01:33.040 --> 01:35.830
I don't watch
television.

01:35.830 --> 01:38.170
That...mm.

01:38.170 --> 01:40.960
Well, that is just gross.

01:40.960 --> 01:42.460
We have all the pieces.

01:42.460 --> 01:44.710
We just need to see
how they all connect.

01:44.710 --> 01:46.620
I can guarantee you they're not
connected by yarn, so...

01:46.620 --> 01:47.880
Okay...

01:47.880 --> 01:49.080
I know they're not connected
by yarn.

01:49.080 --> 01:51.790
The yarn is a metaphoric
connection.

01:51.790 --> 01:53.750
Do you know because
you are connecting --

01:53.750 --> 01:55.080
Sweet murder board.
Aah!

01:58.540 --> 02:00.330
Yvette.

02:00.330 --> 02:01.500
Still as pretty as
a damn picture.

02:01.500 --> 02:03.880
Get in here.

02:03.880 --> 02:05.710
[ Sniffs ]

02:05.710 --> 02:07.290
[ Sniffs ]

02:07.290 --> 02:10.000
You got a jumpy one
on your hands, huh?

02:14.040 --> 02:15.750
So sorry about this,
buddy.

02:15.750 --> 02:17.540
I mean, this is
a work of art.

02:17.540 --> 02:18.710
Solid yarn work.

02:18.710 --> 02:20.960
Dave, what are you
doing here?

02:20.960 --> 02:22.420
Dave?

02:22.420 --> 02:23.880
You know him?

02:23.880 --> 02:26.040
He's one of you?!

02:26.040 --> 02:27.250
Oh, yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:27.250 --> 02:29.080
Big time. Th-That's --
That's why I'm here.

02:29.080 --> 02:30.210
I want to join
Team Kevin.

02:30.210 --> 02:32.000
Join? I-I-I don't know --
Great!

02:32.000 --> 02:33.750
What?

02:33.750 --> 02:37.000
It would be nice if we got some
fresh eyes on this stuff.

02:37.000 --> 02:39.880
And I like the idea of having
my own team.

02:39.880 --> 02:40.880
Team Kevin forever,
right?

02:40.880 --> 02:41.960
[ Laughs ]
Excuse me.

02:41.960 --> 02:43.880
Quick sidebar.

02:43.880 --> 02:45.880
Well, I want in.
I mean...

02:45.880 --> 02:47.330
Okay, we're just gonna...

02:47.330 --> 02:48.830
...we are Team Kevin,
after all.

02:48.830 --> 02:52.620
♪♪

02:52.620 --> 02:54.750
Where are we?

02:54.750 --> 02:57.120
Italia.

02:57.120 --> 02:59.120
Si pravi bellissimo, no?

02:59.120 --> 03:00.920
Get those stupid-ass
sunglasses

03:00.920 --> 03:03.250
off your stupid-ass face.

03:03.250 --> 03:06.000
I have been
working nonstop

03:06.000 --> 03:08.380
while you've been chilling
in Italy?

03:08.380 --> 03:10.830
And now you want back in
just like that.

03:10.830 --> 03:12.170
You quit on me.

03:12.170 --> 03:13.250
I know.

03:13.250 --> 03:15.170
I was frustrated.

03:15.170 --> 03:16.500
I had to clear my head,

03:16.500 --> 03:18.920
so I wandered around.

03:18.920 --> 03:21.710
And after some exposure
to Earth...

03:21.710 --> 03:22.960
[ Sighs ]

03:22.960 --> 03:24.380
I've come to a conclusion.

03:24.380 --> 03:25.830
And what's that?

03:25.830 --> 03:27.000
I love it here.

03:27.000 --> 03:28.920
Oh, my gosh, the scenery,

03:28.920 --> 03:31.290
the food, the people.

03:31.290 --> 03:33.620
Yvette, we have to save
this place.

03:33.620 --> 03:34.960
I don't know.

03:34.960 --> 03:36.960
Kevin's finally hitting
his stride,

03:36.960 --> 03:39.710
and adding a new voice
to the mix...

03:39.710 --> 03:41.620
Will only make the harmony
sweeter.

03:41.620 --> 03:43.000
Hear me out.

03:43.000 --> 03:44.500
What if I sign on
for the short term --

03:44.500 --> 03:46.920
just until Kevin anoints
the next Righteous?

03:48.500 --> 03:51.040
Look, you and I both know that
success breeds success.

03:51.040 --> 03:52.710
If we can help Kevin,

03:52.710 --> 03:56.290
I'm sure we can get the others
to join us.

03:56.290 --> 03:59.250
Can't have a Team Kevin meeting
without the Team Kevin capt--

04:02.920 --> 04:04.540
What the hell?

04:04.540 --> 04:09.000
♪♪

04:09.000 --> 04:10.960
Kevin.
[ Clears throat ]

04:10.960 --> 04:14.580
David will be helping us out
for the time being.

04:14.580 --> 04:15.580
I'm gonna help you
so hard

04:15.580 --> 04:17.580
it's almost gonna become
unhelpful.

04:17.580 --> 04:19.120
Ah, that's fantastic.

04:19.120 --> 04:21.420
That is...wonderful.

04:21.420 --> 04:24.960
So...what are the chances

04:24.960 --> 04:26.920
of the universe...

04:26.920 --> 04:28.670
granting me the strength
of a thousand men?

04:28.670 --> 04:30.580
Slim to none.

04:30.580 --> 04:32.460
Okay, because I was
coming downstairs,

04:32.460 --> 04:35.670
and I just barely grabbed
the railing and...

04:38.500 --> 04:40.330
That!

04:40.330 --> 04:43.120
That happened!

04:43.120 --> 04:45.170
Super strength.

04:45.170 --> 04:47.040
What if...

04:47.040 --> 04:49.670
the universe wanted you to go
to the hardware store?

04:49.670 --> 04:51.830
Renovation blowout.

04:51.830 --> 04:54.080
I love a blowout.

04:54.080 --> 04:58.620
"Save on replacement parts
for stairs, railings, cabinets."

04:58.620 --> 05:00.540
Pretty obvious, man.

05:00.540 --> 05:03.250
The universe thinks your
sister's house is a trash heap.

05:03.250 --> 05:04.710
We got to spruce
this place up.

05:04.710 --> 05:07.500
Or we need to go
to the hardware store

05:07.500 --> 05:10.210
and see what else
the universe has to say.

05:10.210 --> 05:11.330
Really?

05:11.330 --> 05:13.790
'Cause this backsplash
is painful.

05:17.790 --> 05:20.000
Okay, so you have Reese,
a 101-pound girl.

05:20.000 --> 05:23.540
She's on a catwalk
15 1/2 feet in the air.

05:23.540 --> 05:25.040
When she falls,

05:25.040 --> 05:26.920
it takes her
a hair under a second

05:26.920 --> 05:27.710
to hit the ground.

05:27.710 --> 05:29.460
Kevin is...

05:29.460 --> 05:31.420
10 to 15 feet away.

05:31.420 --> 05:33.710
The speed at which it would
take Kevin

05:33.710 --> 05:35.000
to get into position
to catch the salt --

05:35.000 --> 05:36.670
Wait.

05:36.670 --> 05:38.620
Kevin's the pepper,
right?

05:38.620 --> 05:40.620
It's just...
from where I was standing,

05:40.620 --> 05:42.620
it looked like
she was floating.

05:42.620 --> 05:45.830
She was just hanging there,
waiting for him to catch her.

05:45.830 --> 05:48.380
It was only for a second,
but...

05:48.380 --> 05:50.540
[ Sighs ]

05:50.540 --> 05:53.080
I don't think I'll ever
understand what happened.

05:53.080 --> 05:55.580
Maybe it's ketchup.

05:55.580 --> 05:58.880
Uh, sorry, I-I couldn't help
but overhear your dilemma.

05:58.880 --> 06:00.960
Interesting stuff.

06:00.960 --> 06:03.710
Ignacio DePerro,
Amy Cabrera.

06:03.710 --> 06:05.790
Iggy's a professor
of theology.

06:05.790 --> 06:09.830
What if your salt fell
and the pepper was too far away

06:09.830 --> 06:11.250
and there was just
no way it could make the save,

06:11.250 --> 06:14.170
so salt floats
because ketchup?

06:14.170 --> 06:16.460
Uh, can you explain that?
[ Chuckles ]

06:16.460 --> 06:17.830
No.

06:17.830 --> 06:19.580
No one can. Yeah.

06:19.580 --> 06:22.420
'Cause ketchup
is the unexplained.

06:22.420 --> 06:25.830
Ketchup is wormholes.
Ketchup is meridian lines.

06:25.830 --> 06:28.790
Ketchup is miracles.

06:28.790 --> 06:30.750
Oh.

06:30.750 --> 06:32.170
Okay.

06:32.170 --> 06:33.880
I sound insane to you.

06:33.880 --> 06:35.210
Yeah, a little.
[ Chuckles ]

06:35.210 --> 06:36.880
I've got to get to class.
It was nice to meet you, Iggy.

06:36.880 --> 06:38.290
I'll see you.

06:38.290 --> 06:43.040
♪♪

06:43.040 --> 06:46.540
Pass the ketchup.

06:46.540 --> 06:54.170
♪♪

06:54.170 --> 06:55.540
Stop.

06:55.540 --> 06:57.960
Nail gun.

06:57.960 --> 07:00.120
The universe wants me to buy
a nail gun?

07:00.120 --> 07:02.710
No. I do.

07:02.710 --> 07:05.250
Why hammer when you can bust
a nail all up in that wood?

07:05.250 --> 07:07.380
You make sense.
Go on.

07:07.380 --> 07:10.380
This man has the attention span
of a labradoodle.

07:10.380 --> 07:13.170
If you want to help him,
help him focus.

07:15.790 --> 07:17.210
She's not wrong.

07:17.210 --> 07:19.880
Man: Can I get a manager
at register six?

07:19.880 --> 07:22.620
Manager at register six.
You have other things to take
care of -- real things.

07:22.620 --> 07:24.290
You have made it very clear
that that's how you feel.

07:24.290 --> 07:25.880
That's why I said
you didn't have to come.

07:25.880 --> 07:27.040
[ Cart thuds ]

07:27.040 --> 07:28.080
Kevin?

07:28.080 --> 07:30.500
Hey! [ Chuckles ]

07:30.500 --> 07:33.080
Hey, Mrs. Allen.
[ Chuckles ]

07:33.080 --> 07:33.960
Kevin.

07:33.960 --> 07:35.540
It's been a long time.

07:35.540 --> 07:36.580
How are you?

07:36.580 --> 07:37.790
I'm well.

07:40.670 --> 07:43.540
Uh, I am good, too,

07:43.540 --> 07:45.000
also, as well.

07:45.000 --> 07:45.920
[ Chuckles ]

07:49.420 --> 07:52.380
You ladies buying
some hardware?

07:52.380 --> 07:54.500
Yes, Kevin,
I am renovating my home.

07:54.500 --> 07:55.920
Oh.

07:55.920 --> 07:57.960
That's exciting.

07:57.960 --> 07:59.580
You know what, I actually --
I have to make a call.

07:59.580 --> 08:01.330
So, uh...

08:01.330 --> 08:02.710
I'll talk to you later,
Kevin, okay?

08:02.710 --> 08:03.750
Okay.

08:03.750 --> 08:07.040
I'll be in the car.

08:07.040 --> 08:09.920
Well, back to shopping,
I guess.

08:09.920 --> 08:11.790
It was nice to...

08:11.790 --> 08:14.250
Railings.

08:14.250 --> 08:15.830
That's just what I was
looking for.

08:15.830 --> 08:17.540
[ Inhales sharply ]

08:17.540 --> 08:21.500
A lot to choose from...
railings-wise.

08:21.500 --> 08:22.580
[ Chuckles ]

08:22.580 --> 08:24.880
Oh, actually,
here is my guy.

08:24.880 --> 08:26.330
Oh.

08:26.330 --> 08:27.670
Wow, what are the odds?

08:27.670 --> 08:28.750
We're looking
for the same thing,

08:28.750 --> 08:30.040
and it's the last one.

08:30.040 --> 08:32.210
You -- Are you, uh...
You fixing your stairs, too?

08:32.210 --> 08:34.380
Yes, new railing,
new cabinets --

08:34.380 --> 08:37.120
I'm giving the place
a facelift.

08:37.120 --> 08:40.580
I have a bunch of things
on my to-do list.

08:40.580 --> 08:41.750
Here you go.

08:41.750 --> 08:44.210
[ Grunts ]

08:44.210 --> 08:45.080
You don't have
to do that.

08:45.080 --> 08:46.540
No, no, no, no.
I actually --

08:46.540 --> 08:47.750
I do. Um...

08:47.750 --> 08:49.000
That -- That's okay.

08:49.000 --> 08:51.380
Tell me...

08:51.380 --> 08:53.880
do you need any help
with your to-do list?

08:53.880 --> 08:55.830
[ Nail gun fires ]

08:55.830 --> 08:56.790
What was that?

08:56.790 --> 08:57.670
Dave:
Kevin!

08:57.670 --> 08:59.670
Nail gun!

08:59.670 --> 09:01.620
Kevin!

09:01.620 --> 09:03.210
Kevin!

09:03.210 --> 09:05.580
Um, you said cabinets,
and they're over there.

09:05.580 --> 09:07.920
That's just what I was re--
I was going...

09:07.920 --> 09:09.380
Just a little hint.
[ Chuckles ]

09:09.380 --> 09:10.080
That way.

09:13.080 --> 09:14.500
[ Knock on door ]

09:14.500 --> 09:15.960
I don't know
why you're doing this.

09:15.960 --> 09:17.420
You know this lady
hates you, right?

09:17.420 --> 09:19.580
Yeah, I'm -- I am well aware.
Thank you.

09:19.580 --> 09:22.330
He's doing this because
it's what the universe wants.

09:22.330 --> 09:24.290
And who are we to ask?

09:24.290 --> 09:25.830
But why does
she hate you?

09:25.830 --> 09:27.790
Is it because
of Kristin?

09:27.790 --> 09:31.830
She's had it in for me since
she was my English teacher.

09:31.830 --> 09:33.790
I mean, dating her daughter
didn't help.

09:33.790 --> 09:35.290
Bingo.
But...

09:37.080 --> 09:38.750
Hi.
Kevin?

09:38.750 --> 09:40.210
What are you doing here?

09:40.210 --> 09:42.920
I'm ready to help
with your renovations,

09:42.920 --> 09:45.040
as -- as promised.
[ Chuckles ]

09:45.040 --> 09:46.670
Well, I only agreed
to your offer

09:46.670 --> 09:48.420
because I didn't believe
you'd actually come.

09:50.960 --> 09:52.080
Uh, right.

09:52.080 --> 09:53.540
Well, I am here,
and I'm --

09:53.540 --> 09:54.960
I'm ready to help.

09:54.960 --> 09:57.290
And I don't see
any other volunteers.

10:00.620 --> 10:01.500
Thank you.

10:01.500 --> 10:03.920
♪♪

10:03.920 --> 10:06.960
Oh!

10:06.960 --> 10:08.500
Wow. I-I can't remember

10:08.500 --> 10:10.500
the last time
I was in this house.

10:10.500 --> 10:13.540
August 12, 1999.

10:13.540 --> 10:15.170
You snuck in
and spent the night with Kristin

10:15.170 --> 10:16.960
before you went off
to college.

10:16.960 --> 10:18.790
That...

10:18.790 --> 10:20.290
That does ring a bell.

10:20.290 --> 10:22.710
So, why are you really here,
Kevin?

10:22.710 --> 10:25.460
I hope it's not to win me over,
because that ship has sailed.

10:25.460 --> 10:28.290
Ms. Allen, I don't know
if you know this,

10:28.290 --> 10:31.250
but Kristin and I hashed
our stuff out.

10:31.250 --> 10:34.620
You really have no idea,
do you?

10:34.620 --> 10:35.420
Well, I just --

10:35.420 --> 10:38.120
1997.

10:38.120 --> 10:41.880
You vandalized
my entire front lawn --

10:41.880 --> 10:43.880
windows soaked,
toilet paper in the trees,

10:43.880 --> 10:44.920
the lawn graffiti!

10:44.920 --> 10:46.420
Uh, that wa--
That wasn't me.

10:46.420 --> 10:47.750
Oh, please.

10:47.750 --> 10:49.500
I have it on good authority
that it was you.

10:49.500 --> 10:51.120
Who's your
good authority?

10:51.120 --> 10:52.420
Edward Goodwin.

10:52.420 --> 10:55.620
Well, uh...
I have breaking news for you.

10:55.620 --> 10:57.500
Eddie Goodwin is the one
who trashed your lawn.

10:57.500 --> 10:58.960
[ Chuckles ]

10:58.960 --> 11:00.330
Mm-hmm.
Impossible.

11:00.330 --> 11:02.120
Edward was
my best student.

11:02.120 --> 11:04.420
No, Edward was
a humongous kiss-ass,

11:04.420 --> 11:06.250
but everyone in the school
knew he did it.

11:06.250 --> 11:07.960
I mean, he --
he wouldn't shut up about it.

11:07.960 --> 11:10.460
Ed drove by
as I was cleaning up.

11:10.460 --> 11:12.120
They always return to the scene
of the crime --

11:12.120 --> 11:14.670
serial killers,
arsonists...

11:14.670 --> 11:16.040
sophomores.

11:16.040 --> 11:18.620
Oh, that duplicitous
little worm.

11:18.620 --> 11:19.540
Mm-hmm.

11:19.540 --> 11:21.620
I am so sorry, Kevin.

11:21.620 --> 11:23.040
Oh...

11:23.040 --> 11:26.380
let's just...get past it.

11:26.380 --> 11:29.420
Uh, so, where do you
want to start?

11:29.420 --> 11:32.710
Shall we do stairs
or the cabinets?

11:32.710 --> 11:33.710
What do you want?
Th-The cabinets.

11:33.710 --> 11:34.580
Okay.

11:34.580 --> 11:37.500
♪♪

11:37.500 --> 11:39.120
[ Groans ]

11:39.120 --> 11:41.500
Was Susan always
this...?

11:41.500 --> 11:42.790
Icy?

11:42.790 --> 11:44.750
Mm.
Rigid? Uptight?

11:44.750 --> 11:47.790
Uh, no, she has actually
mellowed over time.
Oof.

11:47.790 --> 11:49.290
Yeah, it was worse.

11:49.290 --> 11:51.790
But it's gonna be good now,
because we've cleared the air,

11:51.790 --> 11:55.000
and now Susan will realize
how lovable I am.

11:55.000 --> 11:57.250
You just want her to like you
so you can get some

11:57.250 --> 11:59.250
brownie points
with her daughter.

11:59.250 --> 12:03.380
Well, I have no control
over that.

12:03.380 --> 12:05.120
Nate's car.

12:05.120 --> 12:06.960
Oh, no! It's game night!

12:06.960 --> 12:13.330
♪♪

12:13.330 --> 12:15.540
Before you say anything,
I'm sorry, okay?

12:15.540 --> 12:16.880
Sorry, sorry, sorry,
sorry, sorry, sorry.

12:16.880 --> 12:18.330
About what?
About...

12:21.420 --> 12:24.830
...not bringing snacks
to game night. [ Sighs ]

12:24.830 --> 12:26.670
Since when do you bring
food home?

12:26.670 --> 12:28.580
Well, I don't,

12:28.580 --> 12:32.000
and I've decided to start
apologizing about it.

12:32.000 --> 12:33.880
Okay. Well --
I'm not proud of it.

12:33.880 --> 12:35.620
Yeah, no.
But don't worry about it.

12:35.620 --> 12:36.880
And you know what? Don't even
worry about game night,

12:36.880 --> 12:37.920
because we can play
without you.

12:37.920 --> 12:39.250
Oh, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

12:39.250 --> 12:40.330
I'm definitely in
for game night.

12:40.330 --> 12:42.080
Um...

12:42.080 --> 12:44.040
I just need to check
on the kitchen.

12:44.040 --> 12:46.170
And see if there are
drinks in there...

12:46.170 --> 12:49.540
for me to drink.

12:49.540 --> 12:51.670
Why did you try to talk him
out of playing?

12:51.670 --> 12:52.710
[ Chuckles ]

12:52.710 --> 12:53.460
Wait for it.

12:53.460 --> 12:55.790
Huh?

12:55.790 --> 12:57.500
How awesome is this?

12:57.500 --> 13:00.040
You...

13:00.040 --> 13:02.290
[ Whispering ]
You fixed everything.

13:02.290 --> 13:04.830
Ah, just trying to earn my keep
here on Team Kevin.

13:04.830 --> 13:06.540
We're not genies, Dave.

13:06.540 --> 13:08.880
Fixing his mess is
not our job.

13:08.880 --> 13:10.250
Huh. Well, that's odd.

13:10.250 --> 13:12.000
I thought our job was
to help Kevin.

13:12.000 --> 13:13.250
This is helping.

13:13.250 --> 13:14.710
I mean, he's got enough
on his plate

13:14.710 --> 13:17.000
without having to fix a bunch
of stuff the universe broke.

13:17.000 --> 13:18.830
That is a great point.

13:18.830 --> 13:19.830
Thank you.

13:19.830 --> 13:21.290
That's a good point.

13:23.830 --> 13:25.880
It's a fair point.

13:31.620 --> 13:32.960
Ooh!

13:32.960 --> 13:36.210
Reese: Leg three.

13:36.210 --> 13:39.000
Really?
Yes.

13:39.000 --> 13:41.210
[ Imitates clock ticking ]
Leg three.

13:41.210 --> 13:42.420
Okay, it doesn't have
to be a human leg.

13:42.420 --> 13:43.750
It could be like a leg --
Whoa, whoa, excuse me.

13:43.750 --> 13:45.170
No, no, no, no, no, no.

13:45.170 --> 13:47.880
One word. One number.
No extra info.

13:47.880 --> 13:50.420
Oh, hey, everyone.
Board Game Kevin showed up.

13:50.420 --> 13:52.080
I was wondering
when he'd get here.

13:52.080 --> 13:53.380
Hey, look, I don't mind
if she gives another clue.

13:53.380 --> 13:54.620
We're just having fun.
Thank you.

13:54.620 --> 13:57.330
Oh, no, no, teammate.
Fun is playing correctly.

13:57.330 --> 13:59.960
You can't just throw out
all of the rules

13:59.960 --> 14:02.960
to make up for giving
a terrible clue.

14:02.960 --> 14:04.380
Ooh!
Okay, now do you see
what I mean?

14:04.380 --> 14:06.620
This is why he's the worst
to play board games with.

14:06.620 --> 14:08.500
Oh, it is awesome
playing games with me

14:08.500 --> 14:10.330
because I actually remember
the rules.

14:10.330 --> 14:12.290
Okay, well,
maybe my memory is shot

14:12.290 --> 14:14.380
because I am so busy
because I'm a single mother

14:14.380 --> 14:15.540
trying to raise a teenager
and a toddler.

14:15.540 --> 14:16.830
Oh, I --

14:16.830 --> 14:18.420
Hey, man, take it easy
on your sister.

14:18.420 --> 14:20.210
It's not her fault
she stinks at all games.

14:20.210 --> 14:21.330
What?!
Ooh!

14:21.330 --> 14:23.000
Both of you!
[ Laughing ] What?!

14:23.000 --> 14:24.500
[ Laughs ]

14:24.500 --> 14:26.670
Look, it's your turn.
Okay, no, it's her turn.

14:26.670 --> 14:28.250
Now, stop giving all
the clues, okay?
You're trying to distract us.

14:28.250 --> 14:30.620
I'm not distracting anybody.
I'm just having a good time.

14:30.620 --> 14:33.580
♪♪

14:33.580 --> 14:35.040
Susan: Okay,
hold it steady.

14:37.670 --> 14:38.880
[ Laughs ]

14:38.880 --> 14:40.460
You are like a pro.

14:40.460 --> 14:42.790
Kristin's father was
useless with tools.

14:42.790 --> 14:43.920
[ Both chuckle ]

14:43.920 --> 14:45.790
Okay, keep pressure on it
until the glue sets.

14:45.790 --> 14:47.210
[ Door opens ]

14:48.460 --> 14:49.620
Oh. Hi, sweetie.

14:49.620 --> 14:50.330
Kevin.

14:50.330 --> 14:51.500
Hey.

14:51.500 --> 14:53.620
Uh, what are you --
What are you doing here?

14:53.620 --> 14:56.580
Just, uh, helping your mom
with some projects.

14:56.580 --> 14:58.080
We, uh --
We fixed the kitchen cabinets.

14:58.080 --> 15:00.420
You want to see?
No, I'm good.

15:00.420 --> 15:01.960
Could you actually just
give us a minute?

15:01.960 --> 15:03.250
Don't move.

15:03.250 --> 15:05.670
The glue needs 15 minutes
to set.

15:05.670 --> 15:07.620
Anything you want to say,
you can say in front of Kevin.

15:07.620 --> 15:09.380
So, you told him?

15:12.080 --> 15:13.460
♪♪

15:13.460 --> 15:15.500
[ Sighs ]

15:15.500 --> 15:18.750
I have cancer --
pancreatic.

15:18.750 --> 15:21.380
Oh, God, I'm so sorry.

15:21.380 --> 15:24.250
No, don't be sorry.
Just help me finish this house.

15:24.250 --> 15:25.750
I've got a good
8 to 14 months

15:25.750 --> 15:26.830
to whip it into shape
for Kristin.

15:26.830 --> 15:28.380
I don't want this house,
though.

15:28.380 --> 15:29.380
I want you.

15:29.380 --> 15:31.210
So if you want to give me
something,

15:31.210 --> 15:32.460
just go back
into treatment.

15:32.460 --> 15:35.620
The thought of one more
doctor's visit --

15:35.620 --> 15:37.670
the needles, the --
the being hooked up to machines,

15:37.670 --> 15:42.330
the vomiting into plastic bins
for what, sweetie?

15:42.330 --> 15:44.580
[ Stammers ] Uh...
Another few months of misery?

15:44.580 --> 15:53.380
♪♪

15:53.380 --> 15:55.580
I'm starting on the tile.
Don't move a muscle.

15:55.580 --> 15:56.670
Okay.

15:56.670 --> 16:00.080
♪♪

16:00.080 --> 16:01.460
Kristin, I am so sorry.

16:01.460 --> 16:04.330
So, my mom's
your new project?

16:04.330 --> 16:05.670
Well, I was just
trying to help.

16:05.670 --> 16:08.120
You want to help?

16:08.120 --> 16:09.670
Get her to go back
into treatment.

16:09.670 --> 16:13.290
♪♪

16:13.290 --> 16:15.080
[ Sighs ]

16:18.040 --> 16:19.330
I-I'm confused, guys.

16:19.330 --> 16:20.460
Does the universe really want me
to make Susan

16:20.460 --> 16:21.580
go back into treatment?

16:21.580 --> 16:23.000
Absolutely not.

16:23.000 --> 16:25.080
You can't force someone to fight
for their life.

16:25.080 --> 16:26.170
Okay,
they have to want it.

16:29.330 --> 16:32.250
Are those the rules?

16:32.250 --> 16:36.210
Free will is the greatest gift
to humans.

16:36.210 --> 16:37.460
Susan's made a choice.

16:37.460 --> 16:38.790
You have to respect it.

16:38.790 --> 16:40.080
So, what, then?

16:40.080 --> 16:42.170
Maybe you get
Susan and Kristin

16:42.170 --> 16:43.960
to reconcile
before she passes.

16:43.960 --> 16:45.670
I'm sorry.
I respectfully disagree

16:45.670 --> 16:47.620
with my distinguished
colleague.

16:47.620 --> 16:49.500
[ Engine starts ]
You have a pitch?

16:49.500 --> 16:51.380
Well, yes.

16:51.380 --> 16:53.460
Susan only has a limited amount
of time on Earth.

16:53.460 --> 16:55.250
I think it's our boy's job
to get this lady

16:55.250 --> 16:58.250
to savor the life she has left,
you know,

16:58.250 --> 17:00.250
really just suck the juice
out of the marrow,

17:00.250 --> 17:02.250
seek out some thrills.

17:02.250 --> 17:04.250
Let me get this
straight.

17:04.250 --> 17:07.210
You want him to take
a fragile woman of ill health,

17:07.210 --> 17:09.420
and what?

17:09.420 --> 17:10.920
Talk her into skydiving?

17:10.920 --> 17:11.880
Running with the bulls?

17:11.880 --> 17:13.330
[ Scoffs ]

17:13.330 --> 17:14.920
Anything that puts
an exclamation point

17:14.920 --> 17:16.250
on her final sentence.

17:16.250 --> 17:18.210
That is a beautiful
sentiment.

17:18.210 --> 17:20.250
And, uh, I'm not
doing any of that

17:20.250 --> 17:22.380
with a cancer person.

17:22.380 --> 17:24.210
[ Engine revving ]

17:26.710 --> 17:28.920
Uh, gas pedal's stuck.

17:28.920 --> 17:29.670
Did one of you do this?

17:29.670 --> 17:32.500
Guilty.

17:32.500 --> 17:33.620
Brake!

17:33.620 --> 17:35.960
Brake, brake, brake, brake,
brake, brake!

17:35.960 --> 17:38.580
I'm not comfortable
with this.

17:38.580 --> 17:40.580
Yeah, I can see why most people
would be worried by it,

17:40.580 --> 17:42.790
but, uh, why you, Kevin?

17:42.790 --> 17:43.960
[ Grunts ]
[ Tires screech ]

17:43.960 --> 17:45.710
Death!
Mechanized death!

17:45.710 --> 17:47.420
[ Horn blaring ]
Maybe!

17:47.420 --> 17:49.250
Today's lesson is math.

17:49.250 --> 17:52.290
Simple equation --
fear minus death equals...?

17:52.290 --> 17:54.210
What?

17:54.210 --> 17:55.790
-Thrills.
-Okay.

17:55.790 --> 17:58.380
Thrills, Kevin.
Fear minus death equals thrills.

17:58.380 --> 17:59.330
Now, you know Yvette's
never gonna let

17:59.330 --> 18:00.420
anything happen to you,

18:00.420 --> 18:02.790
so why aren't you
enjoying that?

18:02.790 --> 18:04.460
I-I-I don't know.

18:04.460 --> 18:05.580
I never thought of that.

18:05.580 --> 18:08.790
Um...

18:08.790 --> 18:11.170
Then let go
of the wheel.

18:11.170 --> 18:13.380
Okay, I let go.
I let go.

18:13.380 --> 18:15.830
Now for the fun part.
Yvette, if you please.

18:15.830 --> 18:18.210
Ohh!

18:18.210 --> 18:19.960
[ Horns blaring ]
Oh, yes!

18:19.960 --> 18:22.330
Oh! Oh! Oh!

18:22.330 --> 18:23.540
Yes!

18:23.540 --> 18:25.080
[ Laughs ]

18:25.080 --> 18:27.380
Oh, wow! Wow!

18:27.380 --> 18:28.620
[ Sighs ]

18:28.620 --> 18:30.120
[ Laughs ]

18:30.120 --> 18:33.250
[ Breathing heavily,
chuckling ]

18:35.960 --> 18:36.960
I want to go again.

18:36.960 --> 18:38.330
Do you understand now?

18:38.330 --> 18:40.460
Kevin, you and Susan
are two very different people

18:40.460 --> 18:41.580
with one thing
in common.

18:41.580 --> 18:44.040
You both care deeply
about Kristin.

18:44.040 --> 18:48.750
Neither of you need to worry
about the future.

18:48.750 --> 18:51.000
Kevin, thanks to us,
your survival is a certainty,

18:51.000 --> 18:52.960
just like Susan's death.

18:52.960 --> 18:54.920
And that feeling that you feel
right now, huh?

18:54.920 --> 18:56.290
That exhilaration?
Yeah.

18:56.290 --> 18:57.540
Don't you think that
Susan deserves

18:57.540 --> 18:59.000
to catch a whiff of that
while she still can?

19:00.540 --> 19:01.420
Whoa.

19:02.500 --> 19:03.790
Coconut water, Nate?

19:03.790 --> 19:07.040
Jazzing things up today
a little bit, Amber.

19:07.040 --> 19:08.750
Ooh.

19:08.750 --> 19:09.880
Yep.

19:09.880 --> 19:11.670
[ Register beeping ]

19:11.670 --> 19:14.540
♪♪

19:14.540 --> 19:15.580
Mm-hmm.

19:15.580 --> 19:17.580
Hmm.

19:17.580 --> 19:19.540
Take one of you.

19:19.540 --> 19:22.880
[ Humming ]

19:22.880 --> 19:23.830
Hi, Nate.
[ Chuckles ]

19:23.830 --> 19:25.580
Kevin.

19:25.580 --> 19:28.210
Thank you.

19:28.210 --> 19:29.620
[ Sighs ]

19:29.620 --> 19:31.830
Amber: Okay.

19:31.830 --> 19:33.670
Oh.

19:33.670 --> 19:35.080
That's quite a snack
you got there.

19:35.080 --> 19:36.250
Thanks.

19:36.250 --> 19:37.750
Oh, also, can I get
two hot dogs

19:37.750 --> 19:39.330
and 16 scratchers,
please?

19:39.330 --> 19:41.290
Okay.
Thank you.

19:41.290 --> 19:43.250
What you got, a banana?
That's cute.

19:43.250 --> 19:44.620
[ Laughs ]
Just trying to eat healthy.

19:44.620 --> 19:47.080
Ohh, not me.

19:47.080 --> 19:51.170
I am eating like
nobody's watching.

19:51.170 --> 19:52.080
How you feeling,
Kevin?

19:52.080 --> 19:53.460
Hmm,
that's a good question.

19:53.460 --> 19:55.210
In a word,
I would say,

19:55.210 --> 19:56.960
"Whoo!"

19:56.960 --> 19:58.380
[ High-pitched ringing ]

19:58.380 --> 20:00.250
Keep blowing.

20:00.250 --> 20:01.250
Keep blowing.

20:01.250 --> 20:02.670
Okay, stop.

20:02.670 --> 20:03.880
[ Sighs ]

20:03.880 --> 20:04.710
You're not drunk.

20:04.710 --> 20:06.250
No, man.

20:06.250 --> 20:08.790
You ever have a moment
when your eyes are just...

20:08.790 --> 20:12.380
opened as wide as possible
to the ways of the world?

20:12.380 --> 20:13.620
What were your eyes
opened to?

20:13.620 --> 20:15.620
The math of life.

20:15.620 --> 20:19.750
Fear divided by death
equals --

20:19.750 --> 20:22.210
Wait, that's not it.
Uh...

20:22.210 --> 20:24.500
Okay, we just need
to stop wasting time

20:24.500 --> 20:27.420
and grab life
by its stones, Nate.

20:27.420 --> 20:31.330
Just grab it and squeeze
and twist

20:31.330 --> 20:33.120
and just see what
comes out.

20:33.120 --> 20:34.710
Okay,
that's a terrible analogy.

20:34.710 --> 20:36.290
And good luck.

20:36.290 --> 20:38.880
Well, I'm not just talking
about myself.

20:38.880 --> 20:40.880
When are you gonna
ask Amy out?

20:40.880 --> 20:42.000
What?

20:42.000 --> 20:43.250
Hmm?

20:43.250 --> 20:44.790
We're just...friends,
Kevin.

20:44.790 --> 20:45.790
That's all.

20:45.790 --> 20:47.920
That is not all.

20:47.920 --> 20:50.540
There is so much more there,
and it goes both ways, too.

20:50.540 --> 20:52.620
No!

20:52.620 --> 20:55.540
You think so?

20:55.540 --> 20:58.920
Grab, squeeze,
and twist, Nate.

20:58.920 --> 21:04.380
♪♪

21:04.380 --> 21:05.830
Come on, there has
to be something

21:05.830 --> 21:07.330
that you've always
wanted to do

21:07.330 --> 21:09.330
but told yourself
you shouldn't.

21:09.330 --> 21:10.750
Not that --
It doesn't even have
to be that crazy.

21:10.750 --> 21:13.790
Not that I can think of.

21:13.790 --> 21:17.210
Honestly, I-I've never been
a bucket-list kind of person.

21:17.210 --> 21:18.920
It's so cliché.
It's lame.

21:18.920 --> 21:20.250
Think about this --

21:20.250 --> 21:22.540
When everything is said and done
and you look back,

21:22.540 --> 21:26.620
what's one thing
where you can smile and say,

21:26.620 --> 21:29.250
"I gots mine"?

21:29.250 --> 21:30.460
You know?

21:30.460 --> 21:31.710
Uh...

21:31.710 --> 21:32.960
I guess there is
something.

21:32.960 --> 21:34.420
Tell me.

21:34.420 --> 21:38.080
Susan Allen,
what is it that you want?

21:40.080 --> 21:42.120
Vengeance.

21:42.120 --> 21:47.000
[ Motorhead's "Ace of Spades"
plays ]

21:47.000 --> 21:48.620
Ha!

21:48.620 --> 21:51.710
Ohh! [ Laughs ]

21:51.710 --> 21:53.960
I cannot believe you
just did that.

21:53.960 --> 21:55.670
♪ If you like to gamble ♪

21:55.670 --> 21:57.170
♪ I'll tell you I'm your man ♪

21:57.170 --> 21:59.210
♪ You win some, lose some ♪

21:59.210 --> 22:01.000
♪ It's all the same to me ♪

22:01.000 --> 22:04.120
♪♪

22:04.120 --> 22:06.040
♪ I don't share your greed ♪

22:06.040 --> 22:09.040
♪ The only card I need is
the Ace of Spades ♪

22:09.040 --> 22:13.830
♪ The Ace of Spades ♪

22:13.830 --> 22:15.290
Tell me again how this
is building up

22:15.290 --> 22:16.500
the power of your soul.

22:16.500 --> 22:18.880
Good Lord.
Don't be such a square.

22:18.880 --> 22:20.500
This is what Susan wanted.

22:20.500 --> 22:22.210
Besides, it's fun.

22:22.210 --> 22:24.040
Fun can build the soul,
right?

22:25.920 --> 22:28.500
What do you think?

22:28.500 --> 22:30.500
Ohh!

22:30.500 --> 22:32.210
You're an artist.

22:32.210 --> 22:34.330
[ Both laugh ]

22:34.330 --> 22:36.790
Oh, thank you so much
for this, Kevin.

22:36.790 --> 22:37.960
Oh, that's okay.

22:37.960 --> 22:39.500
No, no.

22:39.500 --> 22:42.210
Until very recently,
my life had become...

22:42.210 --> 22:44.250
not great.

22:44.250 --> 22:47.120
You helped me let go
of all that

22:47.120 --> 22:49.670
just for these
few minutes.

22:49.670 --> 22:52.670
And I had no idea how badly
I needed this until now.

22:52.670 --> 22:54.420
[ Chuckles ]

22:54.420 --> 22:57.420
You've really made a big
difference in my life.

22:57.420 --> 22:59.080
I wanted to make sure
you knew that.

22:59.080 --> 23:01.580
I am really glad
to hear that.

23:01.580 --> 23:05.040
That is how
you build a soul.

23:05.040 --> 23:07.210
[ Sighs ]

23:07.210 --> 23:08.790
[ Chuckles ]
Suck it, Eddie Goodwin!

23:08.790 --> 23:11.750
[ Music resumes ]

23:11.750 --> 23:13.620
[ Screams, laughs ]
What the hell?!

23:13.620 --> 23:15.620
I gots mine!

23:15.620 --> 23:17.750
[ Laughs ]

23:17.750 --> 23:19.080
Is that a penis?

23:19.080 --> 23:21.170
Yeah! Yeah, it is!
[ Laughing ]

23:21.170 --> 23:22.580
Uh, we need to get
out of here.

23:22.580 --> 23:24.670
No.

23:24.670 --> 23:26.250
[ Laughing continues ]

23:26.250 --> 23:27.000
We got to go.

23:27.000 --> 23:28.920
I'm too tired to run.

23:28.920 --> 23:30.120
Oh, my God.

23:30.120 --> 23:31.750
Okay, leave this to me.

23:31.750 --> 23:33.210
[ Squeals ]

23:33.210 --> 23:35.290
♪♪

23:42.290 --> 23:43.670
Professor?

23:43.670 --> 23:46.000
No extensions,
and no extra credit.

23:46.000 --> 23:47.250
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

23:47.250 --> 23:47.920
Hi.

23:47.920 --> 23:50.380
I, uh...

23:50.380 --> 23:52.290
brought you something.

23:52.290 --> 23:55.710
It's about the intersection
of miracles and science.

23:55.710 --> 23:57.750
I'm sorry, but...

23:57.750 --> 24:01.210
I'm not really interested in,
you know, crackpot theories.

24:01.210 --> 24:02.210
Oh.

24:02.210 --> 24:04.500
Uh, it's...my book.
I wrote it.

24:04.500 --> 24:05.670
Oh.

24:05.670 --> 24:08.460
Uh, well, books are --
They're treasures.

24:08.460 --> 24:10.210
I'm just messing with you.

24:10.210 --> 24:11.620
[ Laughs ]
I...

24:11.620 --> 24:14.040
No, but, the, uh --
the actual author's quite good,

24:14.040 --> 24:16.330
and it cites
more than a few cases

24:16.330 --> 24:18.500
that mirror
your own experience.

24:18.500 --> 24:21.250
Well, my experience
wasn't a miracle.

24:21.250 --> 24:24.040
Well, how do you
truly know?

24:24.040 --> 24:26.710
Because miracles
aren't a thing.

24:26.710 --> 24:29.460
They're just events that
science hasn't explained yet.

24:29.460 --> 24:31.250
Well, I mean,
that's the beauty of a miracle.

24:31.250 --> 24:33.830
It's not about religion.
It's about mystery.

24:33.830 --> 24:35.170
Oh, I hate that.

24:35.170 --> 24:38.000
No, that's literally why
I became a scientist.

24:38.000 --> 24:40.920
Okay, so let's do
some science, then.

24:40.920 --> 24:42.250
Take me back to where
it happened.

24:42.250 --> 24:45.380
We'll take measurements,
test every logical explanation,

24:45.380 --> 24:46.580
and if we can't
find one...

24:46.580 --> 24:47.880
We'll find an example
of something

24:47.880 --> 24:49.420
that science hasn't
explained yet.

24:49.420 --> 24:52.790
Or you'll have begun your slide
into the realm of crackpots.

24:52.790 --> 24:54.250
Not a chance.
[ Laughs ]

24:54.250 --> 24:55.210
Okay, but you're on.

24:56.620 --> 25:04.250
♪♪

25:04.250 --> 25:05.120
I hope you order
a grilled cheese

25:05.120 --> 25:06.790
better than you play
Codenames.

25:06.790 --> 25:08.250
Wait till next time.

25:08.250 --> 25:09.750
We'll switch partners.

25:09.750 --> 25:11.670
I'll take Kevin,
and you can take mom.

25:11.670 --> 25:13.380
Thank you.

25:13.380 --> 25:15.000
I had a really good time
with you guys the other night.

25:15.000 --> 25:17.540
Yeah, me, too.

25:17.540 --> 25:20.580
Well, I had such a good time
that I started wondering

25:20.580 --> 25:24.420
how you would feel
if I asked your mother out...

25:24.420 --> 25:27.170
on a -- on a date.

25:27.170 --> 25:29.250
Oh.

25:29.250 --> 25:30.960
I know that this is probably

25:30.960 --> 25:32.960
a really big step
for both of you,

25:32.960 --> 25:35.460
and I would never do anything
if it made you uncomfortable,

25:35.460 --> 25:38.170
so, I don't know,
what do you think?

25:39.960 --> 25:41.710
So...no.

25:41.710 --> 25:43.540
♪♪

25:43.540 --> 25:44.580
No?

25:44.580 --> 25:46.250
No.

25:46.250 --> 25:48.460
Thank you.

25:48.460 --> 25:49.750
Oh. Okay.

25:49.750 --> 25:59.830
♪♪

25:59.830 --> 26:01.880
Hmm, what I wouldn't give

26:01.880 --> 26:04.000
to see Eddie Goodwin's face
right about now.

26:04.000 --> 26:06.170
[ Laughs ]
The little bitch.

26:06.170 --> 26:09.670
[ Laughs ]
Susan, you have
a terrifying dark side,

26:09.670 --> 26:10.540
and I like it.

26:10.540 --> 26:12.040
[ Laughs ]

26:12.040 --> 26:13.040
Score one for
Team Kevin.

26:13.040 --> 26:15.500
High five.

26:15.500 --> 26:18.120
Ahh.

26:18.120 --> 26:19.580
Come on.
Don't leave me hanging.

26:19.580 --> 26:22.380
If we were done here,
Kevin would have had a vision.

26:22.380 --> 26:24.210
And there's been
no vision yet,

26:24.210 --> 26:26.960
[Shouting]
has there, Kevin?

26:26.960 --> 26:28.670
She's right.

26:28.670 --> 26:30.460
We got to turn this party
up a notch.

26:30.460 --> 26:32.040
Hook this lady up
to some bungee.

26:32.040 --> 26:33.670
[ Door opens ]

26:33.670 --> 26:34.960
What the hell
are you doing?

26:34.960 --> 26:36.790
Mm! Day drinking with
your high-school sweetheart.

26:36.790 --> 26:38.210
Why don't you join us?

26:38.210 --> 26:40.120
Did you trash Ed Goodwin's house
last night?

26:40.120 --> 26:41.670
What? No.
Of course not.

26:41.670 --> 26:43.500
Oh, well, that's -- that's --
that's really funny

26:43.500 --> 26:45.580
because Ed recently installed
a security camera

26:45.580 --> 26:49.460
on his front step.

26:49.460 --> 26:50.670
What do you have
to say now?

26:50.670 --> 26:52.830
Oh...my God.

26:52.830 --> 26:55.420
Susan, how could you?

26:55.420 --> 26:58.330
Y-- Eddie Goodwin is
a villain and a vandal.

26:58.330 --> 27:00.250
Ed is a respected member
of the community,

27:00.250 --> 27:02.250
and you burned a penis
into his lawn.

27:02.250 --> 27:04.330
He burned boobs
into my front lawn.

27:04.330 --> 27:05.670
His kids
are in my class.

27:05.670 --> 27:07.170
Boobs!

27:07.170 --> 27:08.830
He was gonna call
the cops.

27:08.830 --> 27:11.250
I had to tell him you were dying
and hopped up on pain meds.

27:11.250 --> 27:12.250
Ooh, you played
the cancer card.

27:12.250 --> 27:13.830
Nice! [ Laughs ]
Great.

27:15.500 --> 27:17.080
'Kay, you know what?
Just -- Just forget it.

27:17.080 --> 27:18.670
Enjoy your happy hour.

27:18.670 --> 27:19.960
Honey...

27:19.960 --> 27:21.580
Hey.

27:21.580 --> 27:23.250
♪♪

27:23.250 --> 27:24.880
Kristin, your mom
just wants

27:24.880 --> 27:26.540
to live the last year
of her life

27:26.540 --> 27:27.790
the way she wants to live it,
okay?

27:27.790 --> 27:28.960
Oh, so she's spending it
running around,

27:28.960 --> 27:30.920
acting like an idiot
with you?

27:30.920 --> 27:31.960
Isn't that her choice?

27:31.960 --> 27:33.960
She's my best friend.
No, I know.

27:33.960 --> 27:36.710
When my dad ran off,
she didn't miss a beat.

27:36.710 --> 27:40.790
She -- She just sacrificed
her entire life for us --

27:40.790 --> 27:42.210
working for us
and -- and --

27:42.210 --> 27:43.710
and fighting for us
to have the same thing

27:43.710 --> 27:45.120
that every other kid had,
and what?

27:45.120 --> 27:46.710
I don't get to fight
for her?

27:46.710 --> 27:48.120
I don't -- What?
I'm supposed to just, what?

27:48.120 --> 27:49.750
Let her fade away?

27:49.750 --> 27:51.710
No, no, no,
but you're wasting time --

27:51.710 --> 27:53.170
yours and your mom's.

27:53.170 --> 27:55.540
You need to realize
that she --
Don't! Don't!

27:55.540 --> 27:57.210
[ Voice breaking ]
Please don't help me.

27:57.210 --> 28:02.790
♪♪

28:02.790 --> 28:06.170
Go back outside
and enjoy the party, okay?

28:06.170 --> 28:08.750
I got to go clean up
her mess.

28:08.750 --> 28:10.000
I...

28:10.000 --> 28:11.790
[ Sighs ]

28:11.790 --> 28:13.790
[ Door slams ]

28:13.790 --> 28:16.330
♪♪

28:19.580 --> 28:20.580
You're bumming me
out, man.

28:20.580 --> 28:21.580
I could snap my fingers
and clean up

28:21.580 --> 28:22.540
Eddie Goodwin's
lawn myself,

28:22.540 --> 28:23.620
and you could go back

28:23.620 --> 28:24.830
to what you're supposed
to be doing,

28:24.830 --> 28:26.210
which is not yard work.

28:26.210 --> 28:28.330
This isn't about yard work,
okay?

28:28.330 --> 28:31.000
I guess I just got so caught up
in helping Susan

28:31.000 --> 28:32.380
I totally lost sight

28:32.380 --> 28:33.790
of what I might be
putting Kristin through.

28:33.790 --> 28:36.290
I agree, Kevin.

28:36.290 --> 28:38.040
So happy with
yourself.

28:39.830 --> 28:40.710
Kevin: Hey, Nate.

28:40.710 --> 28:43.290
Uh, Amy is not home.

28:43.290 --> 28:46.250
Not here to talk to Amy.
I'm here for you.

28:46.250 --> 28:48.670
Dude, you set me up.

28:48.670 --> 28:50.670
Wait, did Amy
turn you down?

28:50.670 --> 28:51.920
No, I didn't ask her.

28:51.920 --> 28:53.120
I talked to Reese.

28:53.120 --> 28:54.290
[ Scoffs ]

28:54.290 --> 28:55.460
Why would you talk
to Reese?

28:55.460 --> 28:56.710
I couldn't just
ask Amy out.

28:56.710 --> 28:58.290
I had to make sure Reese
was okay with it.

28:58.290 --> 28:59.500
Oh, my God!

28:59.500 --> 29:01.920
You are...
such a nice guy.

29:01.920 --> 29:03.380
[ Scoffs ]
Seriously.

29:03.380 --> 29:05.000
You would be, like,
the perfect boyfriend.

29:05.000 --> 29:06.620
I don't know
why I listen to you.

29:06.620 --> 29:09.080
No, I -- Because, look,
I-I'll talk to Reese, okay?

29:09.080 --> 29:11.580
Because there's got to be
another explanation.

29:12.960 --> 29:14.290
♪♪

29:14.290 --> 29:16.670
You doing some
landscaping?

29:16.670 --> 29:18.710
Nope. [ Sighs ]

29:18.710 --> 29:22.120
[ Vehicle approaching ]

29:27.080 --> 29:28.500
[ Engine turns off ]

29:31.250 --> 29:32.540
Hey.

29:32.540 --> 29:34.580
Hey, you don't have
to do this.

29:34.580 --> 29:36.790
I've got a-a ladder.
Let me help.

29:36.790 --> 29:38.170
Yeah, yeah.
No, thank you

29:38.170 --> 29:40.500
'Cause I've already seen
what your help looks like, so...

29:40.500 --> 29:42.290
Uh...

29:42.290 --> 29:44.830
Oh, there's Eddie.

29:44.830 --> 29:45.830
Hey, Eddie.

29:48.250 --> 29:49.120
Just gonna stand there
and watch us.

29:49.120 --> 29:51.420
That's cool.

29:51.420 --> 29:54.790
Are you sure you don't
want some help?

29:54.790 --> 29:57.000
I mean, some of it's
pretty high up.

30:01.670 --> 30:07.750
I think that
is the last of it.

30:07.750 --> 30:10.170
I wish you'd told me
your mom was sick.

30:10.170 --> 30:13.420
Why?

30:13.420 --> 30:15.830
Well...because,

30:15.830 --> 30:17.330
I don't know, that --

30:17.330 --> 30:20.580
It's a lot to deal with
by yourself.

30:20.580 --> 30:22.290
[ Inhales through teeth ]

30:22.290 --> 30:25.540
Yeah, uh,
I-I guess I-I-I just thought

30:25.540 --> 30:29.920
that I would convince her
to go back into treatment.

30:31.830 --> 30:34.460
And, uh...

30:34.460 --> 30:35.830
talking about it just
kind of makes

30:35.830 --> 30:37.460
everything seem...

30:39.790 --> 30:41.210
...inevitable.

30:45.920 --> 30:50.330
Plus, I didn't know how long
you'd be sticking around, so...

30:50.330 --> 30:53.000
Yeah, uh...

30:53.000 --> 30:55.460
that makes sense.

30:55.460 --> 30:57.710
Look, I know that I seem
really selfish,

30:57.710 --> 30:58.880
and, um...

30:58.880 --> 31:00.500
and I-I --

31:00.500 --> 31:02.000
You know, I understand
why she wants to stop,

31:02.000 --> 31:03.460
because the chemo, like,
it really --

31:03.460 --> 31:08.170
[ voice breaking ] it's --
it is worse than the illness.

31:08.170 --> 31:09.920
And it was never gonna be
a cure, you know?

31:09.920 --> 31:11.250
It was just, uh...

31:11.250 --> 31:13.670
It was just a delay.

31:13.670 --> 31:15.710
♪♪

31:15.710 --> 31:17.080
But, yeah, um...

31:17.080 --> 31:18.420
you know, more --
I just --

31:18.420 --> 31:19.540
more than that,
I want her to be happy.

31:19.540 --> 31:21.880
So, you know.

31:25.290 --> 31:28.880
Could I -- Could I see
that security video again?

31:28.880 --> 31:29.750
Uh...

31:29.750 --> 31:30.830
Just...

31:30.830 --> 31:33.420
Sure.

31:33.420 --> 31:34.540
Yeah.

31:40.080 --> 31:42.170
[ Chuckles ]

31:42.170 --> 31:43.540
I mean, she looks
pretty happy to me.

31:43.540 --> 31:45.750
[ Laughs ]

31:45.750 --> 31:48.750
Yeah, she does.

31:48.750 --> 31:50.750
[ Both laugh ]

31:50.750 --> 31:53.750
♪♪

31:53.750 --> 31:56.920
[ Door closes ]

31:56.920 --> 31:59.120
Is there enough
for two?

31:59.120 --> 32:01.540
I'm not up
for a fight today.

32:01.540 --> 32:02.460
Me, neither.

32:07.750 --> 32:10.880
Thank you.

32:10.880 --> 32:13.250
I'm sorry
if I embarrassed you.

32:13.250 --> 32:15.170
Actually, uh...

32:15.170 --> 32:17.250
you impressed me.

32:17.250 --> 32:18.920
The way you took out
Eddie's mailbox --

32:18.920 --> 32:21.540
[exhales sharply]
you got a beautiful swing.

32:21.540 --> 32:22.670
[ Chuckles ]

32:22.670 --> 32:24.380
It's all in the hips.

32:24.380 --> 32:26.830
[ Laughs ]

32:26.830 --> 32:29.420
You know, I, um --

32:29.420 --> 32:32.120
I always thought you could
take that wall out,

32:32.120 --> 32:35.170
just open this room up.

32:35.170 --> 32:37.920
Yeah, you're right.
Better flow.

32:37.920 --> 32:40.750
♪♪

32:40.750 --> 32:43.790
♪ And if the sun starts setting,
the sky won't fall ♪

32:43.790 --> 32:46.920
♪ Even if the clouds get heavy
and start to fall ♪

32:46.920 --> 32:50.210
♪ I really need somebody
to call my own ♪

32:50.210 --> 32:53.040
♪ I wanna be somebody
to someone ♪

32:53.040 --> 32:54.880
♪ Someone to you ♪

32:54.880 --> 32:55.960
[ Both laugh ]

32:55.960 --> 32:58.040
♪ Someone to you ♪

32:58.040 --> 33:00.710
Wait, that wasn't
a load-bearing wall, was it?

33:00.710 --> 33:02.620
Your problem.
Not mine.

33:02.620 --> 33:05.620
♪ Someone to you ♪

33:05.620 --> 33:08.880
♪ Someone to you ♪

33:08.880 --> 33:11.040
[ Insects chirping ]

33:11.040 --> 33:12.790
[ Music playing
through headphones ]

33:12.790 --> 33:16.040
[ Keyboard clacking ]

33:16.040 --> 33:18.580
Hey.

33:18.580 --> 33:20.120
Hey.

33:20.120 --> 33:21.960
How are you?

33:21.960 --> 33:23.460
Fine.

33:23.460 --> 33:24.580
Cool.

33:24.580 --> 33:26.750
Um...

33:26.750 --> 33:28.330
Did you...

33:28.330 --> 33:31.290
want something?

33:31.290 --> 33:34.080
No.

33:34.080 --> 33:35.880
You know, I-I --
[ Sighs ]

33:35.880 --> 33:38.380
I was just thinking about --
it's probably really weird

33:38.380 --> 33:41.460
for you to think about

33:41.460 --> 33:45.080
your mom having, like,
a personal life.

33:47.250 --> 33:48.670
Feelings and...

33:51.960 --> 33:53.380
...wanting to date.

33:53.380 --> 33:56.040
[ Chuckles ]

33:56.040 --> 33:57.500
Nate talked to you.

33:57.500 --> 33:59.710
I thought
that you liked him.

33:59.710 --> 34:01.880
I do like him.

34:01.880 --> 34:04.120
He's cool.

34:04.120 --> 34:05.500
It's her.

34:05.500 --> 34:06.620
She's not ready.

34:06.620 --> 34:08.080
She'd wreck it.

34:08.080 --> 34:10.380
I -- See, I don't -- I don't
know if that's true, Reese.

34:10.380 --> 34:12.420
You know her, Kevin.

34:12.420 --> 34:15.420
Can you imagine her
dating anybody?

34:15.420 --> 34:17.420
She'd just, like,
talk the whole time

34:17.420 --> 34:19.210
and say stupid stuff.

34:19.210 --> 34:21.540
She can't help it.

34:21.540 --> 34:23.290
Wow, you might be right,
actually. [ Chuckles ]

34:23.290 --> 34:26.210
I am right.

34:26.210 --> 34:28.120
So, you're, like, pretty smart,
aren't you?

34:28.120 --> 34:29.750
Shut up.

34:29.750 --> 34:31.500
Because, I mean, I look at you,
and you seem dumb,

34:31.500 --> 34:32.790
like, really
not intelligent.

34:32.790 --> 34:34.080
Just, like,
there's nothing going on.

34:34.080 --> 34:36.040
Just a vacant stare,
but actually,

34:36.040 --> 34:38.000
deep down somewhere,
there's, like,

34:38.000 --> 34:39.540
some thoughts being
rubbed togeth--

34:39.540 --> 34:40.880
Okay.

34:40.880 --> 34:43.040
Have a good night.

34:43.040 --> 34:45.380
Dave suggested I take Susan
streaking, but...

34:45.380 --> 34:46.750
[ Scoffs ]
No way.

34:46.750 --> 34:49.330
No normal person wants
to do that.
I know!

34:49.330 --> 34:51.170
And I just don't have
the cardio in me

34:51.170 --> 34:52.250
to do that kind
of running.

34:52.250 --> 34:53.580
Kevin...

34:53.580 --> 34:55.500
Huh?

34:55.500 --> 34:58.330
Oh, hi. Is, uh...

34:58.330 --> 35:00.540
Wait, S-- Sean!

35:00.540 --> 35:01.920
It's, uh --
It's Kevin Finn.

35:01.920 --> 35:03.210
I-I, um...

35:03.210 --> 35:05.210
I was actually looking
for your mom.

35:05.210 --> 35:06.580
Hey, Kevin.

35:06.580 --> 35:07.790
I'm sorry.

35:07.790 --> 35:09.420
Mom passed away
last night.

35:09.420 --> 35:10.790
♪♪

35:10.790 --> 35:12.580
I...

35:12.580 --> 35:14.540
I thought...

35:14.540 --> 35:16.620
She said she could have
more than a year.

35:16.620 --> 35:18.250
I know.

35:18.250 --> 35:20.880
It was in her sleep.

35:20.880 --> 35:23.040
You know, peaceful.

35:23.040 --> 35:25.080
Kristin's here.
Why don't you come inside?

35:25.080 --> 35:27.120
Um...

35:27.120 --> 35:28.960
No. Uh...no.
Than-- Thank you.

35:28.960 --> 35:31.120
No, I don't want to intrude.

35:31.120 --> 35:32.170
Um...

35:32.170 --> 35:33.620
I'm so sorry, Sean.

35:33.620 --> 35:35.250
Yeah.

35:35.250 --> 35:40.500
♪♪

35:46.830 --> 35:48.670
0.79 seconds.

35:48.670 --> 35:50.750
Does the health department
know how you're using

35:50.750 --> 35:51.790
their first-aid dummy?

35:51.790 --> 35:53.210
[ Chuckles ]

35:53.210 --> 35:54.380
Oh, wait, wait, wait,
wait, hold on.

35:54.380 --> 35:55.380
Hold on.
Don't come down.

35:55.380 --> 35:57.170
I-I want to just measure
your distance.

35:57.170 --> 35:59.750
Close your eyes
'cause it's a laser.

35:59.750 --> 36:02.620
[ Beep ]

36:02.620 --> 36:04.420
So, what do you hope to get
from all these measurements?

36:04.420 --> 36:06.540
[ Device beeps ]
Insight.

36:06.540 --> 36:08.170
Yeah, but you lose
possibility.

36:08.170 --> 36:10.710
As long as you don't know,
anything's possible.

36:10.710 --> 36:13.120
♪♪

36:13.120 --> 36:14.710
Can I open my eyes?

36:14.710 --> 36:16.000
No.

36:16.000 --> 36:17.290
What, are you
messing with me?

36:17.290 --> 36:20.210
[ Laughs ] Yes.

36:20.210 --> 36:21.580
Well, if it makes you
feel any better,

36:21.580 --> 36:23.000
I-I don't think
there's anything

36:23.000 --> 36:24.670
that'll ever explain
what happened.

36:24.670 --> 36:26.710
Good! Great!

36:26.710 --> 36:28.960
Now that's an interesting world
to live in.

36:28.960 --> 36:30.790
No, not great.

36:30.790 --> 36:32.670
Annoying. Frustrating.

36:32.670 --> 36:33.830
Look at you.

36:33.830 --> 36:35.210
You're energized.

36:35.210 --> 36:36.170
You're --
You're motivated.

36:36.170 --> 36:37.540
Why?

36:37.540 --> 36:38.830
Because not knowing
isn't comforting,

36:38.830 --> 36:40.170
but it's exciting.

36:40.170 --> 36:41.920
Like going up
a roller coaster

36:41.920 --> 36:45.500
or standing in front
of a smart...

36:45.500 --> 36:48.460
intriguing
engineering professor,

36:48.460 --> 36:50.120
wanting to ask her out,

36:50.120 --> 36:52.710
but not really knowing
how she'd respond.

36:52.710 --> 36:55.170
It's all neck chills
and stomach butterflies.

36:55.170 --> 36:56.750
Yes.

36:56.750 --> 36:58.580
What?

36:58.580 --> 37:00.380
Well, um...

37:00.380 --> 37:02.580
not to remove
any possibilities,

37:02.580 --> 37:05.880
but, um, if you were
to ask me out,

37:05.880 --> 37:07.920
I would --
I would say "Yes."

37:07.920 --> 37:17.290
♪♪

37:17.290 --> 37:19.710
Your boss...

37:19.710 --> 37:22.250
is a jerk.

37:22.250 --> 37:25.540
A lovely and decent
woman dies,

37:25.540 --> 37:28.750
leaving another wonderful woman
devastated.

37:28.750 --> 37:30.330
[ Scoffs ]

37:30.330 --> 37:33.000
You're preaching
to the choir.

37:33.000 --> 37:36.040
All I want is --
is an explanation, okay?

37:36.040 --> 37:38.250
I don't think that
that is too much to ask for.

37:38.250 --> 37:40.830
Yeah, I wish I could
give you one.

37:40.830 --> 37:42.920
But I have my theory.

37:42.920 --> 37:44.080
I think, uh,
God just wants

37:44.080 --> 37:47.830
all of us
to stay occupied.

37:47.830 --> 37:48.880
"Stay occupied"?

37:48.880 --> 37:50.960
Sure.

37:50.960 --> 37:54.080
You know, I mean,
the busier we are doing stuff,

37:54.080 --> 37:55.380
the less questions we ask.

37:55.380 --> 37:57.000
"Why are we here?"

37:57.000 --> 38:00.460
"What are God's plans?"

38:00.460 --> 38:02.210
You know, in the short time
that I've been in this place,

38:02.210 --> 38:06.120
I've, uh --
I've realized something.

38:06.120 --> 38:07.580
I don't think
there is a plan.

38:07.580 --> 38:10.290
[ Vehicle door opens, closes ]

38:13.080 --> 38:14.710
Kristin. Hey.

38:14.710 --> 38:16.040
I'm so sorry.

38:16.040 --> 38:17.920
I-I came by, and --

38:17.920 --> 38:19.670
Yeah. No, I heard.
Thank you.

38:19.670 --> 38:21.120
[ Sniffles ]

38:21.120 --> 38:22.710
Isn't everyone
still there?

38:22.710 --> 38:24.420
Yeah. [ Chuckles ]

38:24.420 --> 38:27.920
Um, my family is --
is great.

38:27.920 --> 38:31.080
But -- But, um...

38:31.080 --> 38:32.500
But.

38:32.500 --> 38:36.540
♪♪

38:36.540 --> 38:40.710
So, I-I went for a drive,
and, um...

38:40.710 --> 38:43.500
my car drove me here,
so... [ Chuckles ]

38:45.000 --> 38:47.460
[ Chuckles ] Well...

38:47.460 --> 38:49.120
You don't happen to have another
one of those, do you?

38:49.120 --> 38:50.120
[ Laughs ]
Oh! Yeah!

38:50.120 --> 38:51.580
I have --
I have, uh...

38:51.580 --> 38:52.960
Yeah.

38:52.960 --> 38:55.960
♪♪

38:55.960 --> 38:58.750
Thank you.

38:58.750 --> 39:03.380
[ Sighs deeply ]

39:03.380 --> 39:07.330
She was happy.

39:07.330 --> 39:11.500
You know, and I...
I think it's -- it's really

39:11.500 --> 39:14.290
the most anyone
can wish for in life.

39:14.290 --> 39:16.080
♪♪

39:16.080 --> 39:18.710
Yeah,
I hope I'm so lucky.

39:18.710 --> 39:24.330
♪♪

39:24.330 --> 39:27.290
I'm really glad that you're not
just passing through.

39:31.670 --> 39:34.500
Me, too.

39:34.500 --> 39:36.500
[ Inhales deeply ]

39:36.500 --> 39:38.460
Oh, wow.
Look at the sunset.

39:38.460 --> 39:40.210
It's beautiful.

39:40.210 --> 39:49.210
♪♪

39:49.210 --> 39:51.210
It's incredible.

39:51.210 --> 39:56.620
♪♪

39:56.620 --> 40:02.330
♪♪

40:02.330 --> 40:04.040
Let me start this meeting
by saying

40:04.040 --> 40:05.420
Team Kevin
is kicking ass.

40:05.420 --> 40:07.120
Yes!
[ Laughs ]

40:07.120 --> 40:09.580
Yvette, while the rest of us
were unsure,

40:09.580 --> 40:12.670
you were the one who correctly
identified our goal.

40:12.670 --> 40:13.710
Okay, wonderful.
Now let's talk about --

40:13.710 --> 40:15.790
But, Dave,
it was your methods,

40:15.790 --> 40:18.460
unconventional as
they may be,

40:18.460 --> 40:22.040
that really got us
to achieve those goals.

40:22.040 --> 40:25.670
And that is why you are...

40:25.670 --> 40:28.620
Team Kevin's
Player of the Game.

40:28.620 --> 40:30.040
Whoa.

40:30.040 --> 40:32.920
Whoa.

40:32.920 --> 40:34.080
You must have so many
gold stars.

40:34.080 --> 40:36.790
Uh, this is a new thing.

40:36.790 --> 40:40.380
Well, what we need to remember
is that we are a great team.

40:40.380 --> 40:41.670
Hell, yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

40:41.670 --> 40:44.420
Uh, Kevin, if --
if you'll excuse Yvette and I

40:44.420 --> 40:46.380
for just a sec...?

40:46.380 --> 40:47.960
I'm not even gonna try
to follow you.

40:47.960 --> 40:50.710
Yvette: [ Sighs ]

40:50.710 --> 40:52.080
You know what,
we'll skip the glasses

40:52.080 --> 40:54.670
and drink straight
from the tap.

40:54.670 --> 40:55.880
[ Cork pops ]
Fore!

40:55.880 --> 40:57.500
[ Cork splashes ]

41:01.420 --> 41:04.290
Hey, um...look,
I know this is hard for you.

41:04.290 --> 41:05.620
You've been working
your ass off,

41:05.620 --> 41:06.880
and all of a sudden,
there's a new baby,

41:06.880 --> 41:08.210
and he gets a gold star
and --

41:08.210 --> 41:09.960
Oh, I -- Oh, I don't --
I don't care about a gold star.

41:09.960 --> 41:11.120
Yeah, no, I-I know.

41:11.120 --> 41:12.620
Yeah, well, you know,
but you do.

41:12.620 --> 41:13.960
You do. You do.
A little bit.

41:13.960 --> 41:16.380
It's a gold star,
so...

41:16.380 --> 41:19.380
[ Birds sing in distance ]

41:21.420 --> 41:23.620
To Team Kevin.

41:23.620 --> 41:25.460
You see,
that's what I'm talking about.

41:25.460 --> 41:27.040
With the two of us putting
our talents together,

41:27.040 --> 41:29.000
we'll guide Kevin
to the Righteous in no time.

41:29.000 --> 41:30.460
Yeah, but we don't have
that luxury.

41:30.460 --> 41:31.790
What are you talking about?

41:31.790 --> 41:32.880
You and I both know
the clock is ticking

41:32.880 --> 41:34.540
on this whole situation.

41:34.540 --> 41:36.620
You want to save this place?
We need to act quickly.

41:36.620 --> 41:38.620
[ Sighs ]

41:38.620 --> 41:40.380
You have...

41:40.380 --> 41:42.830
talents, Dave --

41:42.830 --> 41:45.000
skills I don't have.

41:45.000 --> 41:48.040
Well, this is true.

41:48.040 --> 41:51.750
Trivia night, origami,
interpretive dance,

41:51.750 --> 41:54.920
sensual massage, welding,
drawing circles.

41:54.920 --> 41:56.330
Interpersonal skills.

41:56.330 --> 41:59.210
You have the gift of sales,
Dave.

41:59.210 --> 42:01.380
And we need to put those skills
to the test.

42:01.380 --> 42:02.580
How so?

42:02.580 --> 42:07.210
♪♪

42:07.210 --> 42:08.500
I have a mission for you.

42:13.420 --> 42:22.790
♪♪

42:22.790 --> 42:32.420
♪♪

42:32.420 --> 42:41.830
♪♪
